unset.gif" border=0></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uleopapanthera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leopa Panthera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight</span><br> <font color=#00F500>(1/15/02 12:19:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=393.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why Vazaelle?</span><hr size=1> I still have Amyzon, but she's not in her original incarnation. When I made her, I put the points in all of the stats like 5 in WIS, 5 in CHA, and so on. No big deal really. I got her up to level 12 before I realized my &quot;mistake.&quot; I made Leopa to get away from someone who was bothering me on a nightly basis, not as a &quot;re-roll.&quot; I did decide that I really should have played a cleric since I usually filled the healing role in groups (love my druid, but cleric describes what I usually do) so I consider Pedi as my actual &quot;re-roll.&quot;<br><br>I did play other classes/combinations before settling on my druid and cleric. I also deleted Amyzon and restarted her with the stats in the proper categories. I got her up to level 22 before I realized that I just didn't have the interest in being a really good puller, tanker, etc. Just enjoyed healing, buffing, and helping others do the best job they can. I'll never delete Amyzon though! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uabinsuranautishzaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abinsuran Autishzaar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hero</span><br> 